sentences: Joy Lynn White (born July 24, 1961) is an American country music singer-songwriter.
Signed to Columbia Records in 1992, she released her debut album Between Midnight & Hindsight that same year.
In 1993, she was nominated for Top New Female Vocalist at the Academy of Country Music Awards, but lost to Michelle Wright.
